Text: A patient had 2 total visits to the hospital. On visit 1, they had the following diagnoses: Age-related osteoporosis without current pathological fracture, Angiodysplasia of stomach and duodenum without bleeding, Anxiety disorder, unspecified, Diaphragmatic hernia without obstruction or gangrene, Dysphagia, unspecified, Gastro-esophageal reflux disease without esophagitis, Nonrheumatic mitral (valve) prolapse, Other specified symptoms and signs involving the circulatory and respiratory systems, Personal history of nicotine dependence. On visit 2, which was 672 days after the previous visit, the patient had the following diagnoses: Activity, walking an animal, Age-related osteoporosis without current pathological fracture, Anxiety disorder, unspecified, Fall on same level from slipping, tripping and stumbling without subsequent striking against object, initial encounter, Gastro-esophageal reflux disease without esophagitis, Long term (current) use of anticoagulants, Migraine, unspecified, not intractable, without status migrainosus, Nonrheumatic mitral (valve) prolapse, Personal history of nicotine dependence, Personal history of urinary calculi, Pure hypercholesterolemia, unspecified, Sidewalk as the place of occurrence of the external cause, Unspecified intracapsular fracture of left femur, initial encounter for closed fracture.
